11. KEY TAKEAWAYS
================================================================================

1. MODEL MATTERS MORE THAN CLIENT
   Claude (78.7%) >> Deepseek (27.9%–59.7%). The model is the dominant factor.

2. CLIENT MATTERS MORE THAN EXPERIMENT VARIANT
   Same Deepseek model: RooCode 59.7% vs 5ire 27.9%. Client architecture alone = 2.1x.

3. HARD CHALLENGES ARE THE BOTTLENECK
   Easy: 75.7% → Medium: 60.2% → Hard: 30.6%. Hard challenges need decomposition,
   checkpoints, and multi-step tool chains that don't exist yet.

4. WEB IS THE WEAKEST CATEGORY
   43.0% overall. Web/Hard at 13.3%. http_framework_test (69.9% failure) and
   browser_agent_inspect (61.7% failure) are the primary blockers.

5. TOOL HALLUCINATION WASTES CONTEXT
   web_request (36 calls, 100% fail) and source_code_read (14 calls, 100% fail)
   are phantom tools that LLMs hallucinate. 50 wasted tool calls total.

6. PWNTOOLS IS UNDERUSED
   pwntools_exploit: 38 uses, 81.6% success. execute_python_script: 1,832 uses,
   77.8% failure. LLMs choose the wrong tool for binary exploitation by 48:1.

7. 5IRE NEEDS ARCHITECTURAL FIXES
   Not just prompt tuning — it misinterprets constraints, leaks native tools,
   and submits empty parameters at rates 2-3x higher than RooCode.

8. 9 CHALLENGES ARE UNSOLVABLE BY ALL CONFIGS
   These require capabilities not yet in HexStrike: multi-step XSS+CSRF chains,
   disk image forensics, advanced crypto (SRA, Secure Dot Product).
